<subSubSection pageNumber="906" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="906">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="906">Note:</emphasis>
Drouet &amp; Daily (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="906">Butler Univ. Bot. Stud.</emphasis>
12: 167. 1956) indicated unspecified material in LINN as the type, and Drouet (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="906">Beih. Nova Hedwigia</emphasis>
57: 219. 1978) stated that the type was &quot;
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Ulvaceae" genus="Ulva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ulvales" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="granulata">Ulva granulata</taxonomicName>
&quot; in LINN. It is unclear which material was intended as the only sheet to carry this name (as an incidental, later annotation) is associated with 
<taxonomicName class="Tremellomycetes" family="Tremellaceae" genus="Tremella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" order="Tremellales" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="906">Tremella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName class="Ulvophyceae" family="Ulvaceae" genus="Ulva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ulvales" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="906">Ulva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is in any case unannotated by Linnaeus, and a post-1753 addition to the herbarium. It is not original material for the name.
</paragraph>
